 In the village of{Upper Hopton}most   
 social activity is centred round the {
{Working Men's Club,}the {Cricket Club}
 the{Church,}the village hall called { 
{Croft House.}There are{Cubs, Brownies,
{Guides , Scouts.}There is a {Youth    
{Club}for teenagers. During the day a {
{Mothers and Toddlers}Club meets and a{
{Playgroup}for children under 5.The{   
{over-6O's}enjoy a social afternoon    
 each week. The{Sunday School}meets    
 each Sunday morning, while worship is 
 conducted in{St John's Church.}The{   
{Mothers Union}also meets weekly.      
 There is an annual {Village Gala}when 
 a Queen is crowned. Children from the 
 village school often dance on this    
 occasion and there are games, sports  
 etc..The{Cricket Club}plays games     
 weekly throughout the summer. This is 
 a thriving village community.
